  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Social Worker",
  "description": "<p>Reporting to the Chief Executive Officer, you will:</p><ul><li>To oversee the administration and operations of the Social Service Department. </li><li>Provide regular updates to next of kins (NOKs) on the beneficiaries and families. </li><li>Support and present cases to the Admission & Review Committee for evaluation and approval for admission to the Home.</li><li>Case Manager for the Individual Care Plan (ICP) of residents, clients and Training in Independent Living (TIL) residents.</li><li>Coordinating admissions & discharge, means testing exercise, coordinate and schedule ICP conferences with beneficiaries and their families/caregivers.</li><li>Liaise with MSWs and/or Doctors or referring agency for relevant medical information especially on present treatment if these have not been given in the application form.</li><li>Conduct regular groupwork with residents and multi-disciplinary team to sort out social problems encountered by residents.</li><li>Maintain records of beneficiaries and manage the Electronic Case Management System (eCMS), and report in EPES on ICP updates.</li><li>In-charge of publicity outreach to relevant Agencies, Hospitals etc. for purpose of increasing the muster for the Residents’ Care and TIL programmes.</li><li>Explore job opportunities for the beneficiaries.</li><li>Compile and provide data to MSF and any other relevant agencies<br /></li></ul><p><u>Requirement:</u></p><ul><li>Registered Social Worker with Bachelor’s or Graduate Diploma in Social Work</li></ul><ul><li>More than 5 years of experience in Social Service Agencies, MOH or NH in similar capacity.</li><li>Experience in leading a small social work team.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
